<br>
First Dulcette, I apologize for not communicating more clearly with you that because this was my FIRST raid, I had no clue as to the following:<br>
<br>
1) Role of group leader<br>
2) Basic responsibility of our group (mostly casters) - i.e. hang back - enter melee (would have thought the former)<br>
3) Group number - never knew if we were 1, 2, or 3<br>
4) After Forich went LD, Thor became our group leader (most exp level 41 Pally)<br>
5) Sorry wasn't even sure what MF1, MF2 were. <br>
6) Did we have a primary objective for the group as a whole?  From where I was (on auto follow of our group leader) - very confusing.<br>
<br>
I never felt our group was in sink, never got a confimation that Thor had been invited into chat.  I suspect after reading the post that it was my job to relay the commands and instructions to my group, after Forich went LD (and later after he quit) - this was never made clear to me during the event.  Our group was listening to Thor for instructions and following him.  I suspect he never was invited to chat, so hence the screw up.  This was MY responsibility to inform you I felt we were lost, and for that my apologies.<br>
<br>
Because this was my first event, it proved to be extremely confusing and disorganized.  I think as a newbie the following would be helpful:<br>
<br>
1)   Some basic instructions should be given on basic RvR play - I learned more in your post today then all of last night.<br>
2)   For me personally, specific instructions as a group healer for RvR play<br>
3)   An understanding of principal objective or plan for overall group.<br>
<br>
I know it proved very dissappointing for many of my close friends who joined me for our first &quot;event&quot;.  Alldric, Uthar, Shaymus and I worked hard over vacation to finally raise our charactes above 30 - this event was what the effort had been for.<br>
<br>
Lets get it right next time <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
