<br>
For the First Timers -<br>
<br>
- I suggest you review the War Room, it really does have alot of great information.<br>
- I have consistently asked that ONE post be made with a pin held to it, that is updated, so that both guilds put the primary things you need to know in it.  If no one wishes to step forward to do this, then I will.  I think this will be a helpful reminder to everyone, as well as ONE place to go for the firstimers.  It would outline the very things you mentioned, Role of Group Leader, basic responsibilties of general classes, etc.<br>
- anyone who has the ability, MAYBE we could take one of the maps that are out there and formulate to read the terms we use.  Sorry I cannot help with this, as I don't have the computer knowledge to do this.<br>
- With regards to the primary objective, I had assumed &lt;I am old enough to know I shouldn't do this&gt; that the objective had been laid out before my arrival.<br>
- Communcation was rather poor last nite.  I couldn't even get confirmation you were LD.  The back-up should immediately tell in /chat who went LD, where and who their new back up is.  When LD's return, they resume their position &lt;ie. Group Leader&gt;.<br>
- I want to make it clear, it is not an embarrassment, if someone wishes to withdraw from a responsiblity until they are ready.  I am an extremely fast typer, in case no one noticed.  This is an asset in RvR.<br>
<br>
With regards to the dissappointment.  I knew this and trust me, those around me knew how upset I was to do what I did.  I took it as a personal failure.  This is my suggestion, all NEWCOMERS should attend a 'small' RvR event before attending a raid, to get a feel for things or even a 'free for all' event where you just port in and get a group.  However, with that said, here is my suggestion.......<br>
<br>
This is my offer to the guild.  I will hold weekly 'one group' RvR events, so that we can learn the lay of the land.  It will be a combination of those who have some experience, along with those who are new.  I say half and half.  Four 'newbies' and Four 'oldtimers'.  I will hold these events on different nites, most being held in the evening around 730pm est or later.  I am open to suggestions.  They will last 2 - 3 hours.<br>
<br>
I only hope the fun you and Alldric experienced a few nites ago, can be conveyed to Uthar, Shaymus, Igraina, etc.  As I would so love to share with them, the adrenaline rushes we felt that nite.<br>
